title: ICE "capacity overflow" during transmutability check

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![crate_type = "lib"] #![feature(transmutability)] #![allow(dead_code)] mod assert { use std::mem::{Assume, BikeshedIntrinsicFrom}; pub struct Context; pub fn is_maybe_transmutable() where Dst: BikeshedIntrinsicFrom {} } fn test() { #[repr(C, align(2))] struct A(u8, u8); #[repr(C)] struct B(u8, u8); assert::is_maybe_transmutable::(); } ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'capacity overflow', library/alloc/src/raw_vec.rs:518:5 ```

### Initial bisect result Doesn't seem to be a recent regression. Goes back at least as far as the introduction of `BikeshedIntrinsicFrom` in e4417cf020fbcd6182c11637bc6b8694434bd81a. ### Version ``` rustc 1.66.0-nightly (0da281b60 2022-10-27) binary: rustc commit-hash: 0da281b6068a7d889ae89a9bd8991284cc9b7535 commit-date: 2022-10-27 host: x86_64-apple-darwin release: 1.66.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.2 ```
